{
  "stem": "12289.3",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But he was our-- accompanied us the whole way till the Finnish border.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So we were under guard the whole way-- the whole way, of course.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But--",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, we were the-- my-- my boss then, the ambassador, myself, and then two others.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Lars Berg, he was the head of the-- he was section for the foreign interests, as I told you, with his next in command, called Carlsson.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We had a Swede called Ekmark, who was in charge of all this buying foodstuffs for-- for the houses under our protection and all that and so on.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We had the two girls, Asta Nilsson, who was the Save the Children representative, Save the Jewish Children.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And-- and Margareta Bauer, who was the secretary at the embassy.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And the chancery officer, Denes von Mezey, he was also with us.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And so I think that's-- that was about it.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 48,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Beg your pardon?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah, Switzerland.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Well, they were-- they were taken.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And that was what I learned when I came home to Sweden.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So my colleague there, he was a young man, like me.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He and the-- the consul they had and-- and two-- and two others, about three or four employees by-- in the-- in the Swiss embassy were all taken, together, brought to-- to the prison, Lubyanka Prison in Moscow.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I think that was the first prison they were taken to.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I met him, of course, after the war, again.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And he was back.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And he said to me that, it was quite clear, from the beginning, that they were taken because the Soviets wanted them as kind of exchange objects in case they-- they would need to get back some of their people.",
      "word_count": 40
    }
  ],
